A = {2, 3, 5, 8}
B = {3, 5, 7}

Intersection of A and B: {3, 5}
A △ B = {2, 8, 7} (elements in A or B but not in their intersection)

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between (A △ B) and the set {5, 7, 9}.

(A △ B) = {2, 8, 7}
C = {5, 7, 9}

Intersection of (A △ B) and C: {7}
(A △ B) △ C = {2, 8, 5, 9} (elements in (A △ B) or C but not in their intersection)

So, the final answer is (A △ B) △ C = {2, 8, 5, 9}.
